0,0.comment: the AUX0 field defines which floor the stairs lead to. if AUX0 < the maze level, it is stairs up; otherwise they are stairs down. fields AUX1 and AUX2 correspond to the x and y positions on the new map level to which the stairs lead

5,9.comment: the AUX0 field defines which floor the transfer leads to. fields AUX1 and AUX2 correspond to the x and y positions on the new map location to which the stairs lead

10,8.comment: the AUX0 field is a flag. if AUX0 === 0, then the elevator takes the party to the same spot on the chosen level. if AUX0 !== 0, then the player is sent to a random x and y on the selected level. the AUX1 field is the lowest level the elevator leads to  (1-10). AUX2 is the highest level (1-10)
